CPU: Intel Core i5-2400

It seems Quaternion::operator== SSE implementation is bugged and always(?) returns false.

This test returns true for me:

``` C++
if (Quaternion::IDENTITY != Quaternion::IDENTITY)
{
    // we have a bug
}
```

Operator != is just:

``` C++
return !(*this == rhs);
```

or

``` C++
if (!(Quaternion::IDENTITY == Quaternion::IDENTITY))
{
    // we have a bug
}
```

Also maybe unit tests should be considered? It can help catch such bugs.

bool Mutex::TryAcquire()
{
    return TryEnterCriticalSection((CRITICAL_SECTION*)handle_) == 0;
}

It gives more freedom when using threads.
